  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      We aim to examine efficacy of a plant stanolester beverage to lower serum cholesterol and
      LDL-cholesterol levels, when given with or without a fatty acid preparation. Study subjects
      are otherwise healthy proctocolectomized ileostoma patients (n=10), who consume stanolester
      beverage with or without a fatty acid preparation in a random order for one week period after
      a standardized low-fat meal. Washout period is 4 weeks. Serum lipids, lipoprotein lipids,
      sterols and fecal sterols and variables of cholesterol metabolism will be examined
      accordingly.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
